# 🧠 Real-world Backend Example (IMPORTANT 🚀)

### ❌ Bad API design

```java
interface UserService {
    void login();
    void register();
    void deleteUser();
    void sendEmail();
}
```

👉 Now every class must implement ALL methods 😵

---

### ✅ Good design (ISP applied)

```java
interface AuthService {
    void login();
    void register();
}

interface UserManagementService {
    void deleteUser();
}

interface NotificationService {
    void sendEmail();
}
```

---

### 👇 Usage

```java
class AuthServiceImpl implements AuthService {
    public void login() {}
    public void register() {}
}

class EmailService implements NotificationService {
    public void sendEmail() {}
}
```

---

# 💡 Real Life Analogy (Never Forget)

Think of a **Remote Control** 📺

❌ Bad:

* One remote has 100 buttons (AC + TV + Washing Machine + Car 😵)

✅ Good:

* Separate remote for each device

👉 You only use what you need

---

# 🧠 Interview Line (IMPORTANT)

> “ISP ensures that clients are not forced to depend on methods they do not use by splitting large interfaces into smaller, more specific ones.”

---

# ⚡ One-line memory trick

👉 **“Make small, specific interfaces — not fat ones.”**

